# Med-AnyLabeling — guidance for AI assistants

**Fork of [AnyLabeling](https://github.com/vietanhdev/anylabeling) by Viet-Anh Nguyen.**
**Maintained by [PaulOkwija](https://github.com/PaulOkwija).**

This is a desktop image-annotation app on PyQt6 with an auto-labeling backend
that runs ONNX models (SAM1/MobileSAM, SAM2, SAM2.1, YOLOv8). The fork's primary
focus is **medical imaging segmentation** with session timing analytics.

## Fork Goals
1. Streamlined UI — remove clutter, keep segmentation workflows front-and-center
2. Session timer built into the annotation workflow
3. Single standalone Windows `.exe` (PyInstaller, zero install friction)

## Conventions
- Use **PyQt6** (not PyQt5).
- macOS path **excludes PyQt6** from `pyproject.toml` (`platform_system != 'Darwin'`);
  macOS users get it via conda. Don't add a Darwin-side floor without changing the
  install story.
- Keep code split into focused files; avoid growing `label_widget.py`
  (already ~3.2k LOC) further when a new widget would do.
- **Simplify, don't add** — for UI, always prefer removing clutter over adding options.

## Architecture Cheat Sheet
- Entry point: `anylabeling/app.py` → `MainWindow` → `LabelingWrapper` →
  `LabelingWidget` (the "god widget" — owns canvas, file list, toolbars).
- Auto-labeling: `anylabeling/services/auto_labeling/`
  - `registry.py` → `@ModelRegistry.register("type-name")` decorator
  - `model_manager.py` → loads `models.yaml`, downloads weights to
    `~/anylabeling_data/models/`, dispatches `predict_shapes_threading()`
  - `models.yaml` (`anylabeling/configs/auto_labeling/`) is the model
    catalog the UI reads. New model = new entry **and** registered class.
- Timing service: `anylabeling/services/timing/` (fork addition)
  - Records per-image and per-session wall-clock time
  - Exports to CSV for downstream efficiency analysis
- CPU/GPU duality: `setup.py` reads `__preferred_device__` from
  `anylabeling/app_info.py`; publish workflows `sed` it before `python -m build`.

## Building the Executable
See `docs/build_executable.md`. Uses PyInstaller + `anylabeling.spec`.
ONNX DLLs are bundled explicitly in the spec. Build from a clean venv.

## Resource Regeneration
- PyQt6 dropped `pyrcc`. To rebuild `anylabeling/resources/resources.py`
  use `python scripts/compile_languages.py` — it shells out to
  `pyside6-rcc` and `pyside6-lrelease` and rewrites imports back to PyQt6.
- `PySide6-Essentials` is a `[dev]` extra for this reason only.

## Pre-Publish Gate
- `.github/workflows/tests.yml` runs a matrix (Ubuntu/Windows/macOS × py3.11/3.12/3.13).
- Always run `python -m unittest discover -s tests` in a fresh venv before tagging.
- See `CLAUDE.md` for the full pre-publish playbook.
